                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15954333" author="mridulm80" created="Mon, 3 Apr 2017 23:33:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is nasty ! This means submissionTime will always be unset ?&lt;br/&gt;
Btw, is it possible for submissionTime to be set - but to an incorrect value ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15954340" author="vanzin" created="Mon, 3 Apr 2017 23:42:01 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is nasty ! This means submissionTime will always be unset ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, it&apos;s a little more complicated than that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The UI code currently &quot;self heals&quot;, because it just keeps a pointer to the &lt;tt&gt;StageInfo&lt;/tt&gt; object which is modified by the scheduler later. So eventually the UI sees the value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the event log, for example, might not have the submission time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Btw, is it possible for submissionTime to be set - but to an incorrect value ?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wouldn&apos;t say incorrect; at worst it&apos;s gonna be slightly inaccurate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15954348" author="mridulm80" created="Mon, 3 Apr 2017 23:48:12 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I wouldn&apos;t say incorrect; at worst it&apos;s gonna be slightly inaccurate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was referring to the case where we are persisting to event log or consuming events to externally persist them.&lt;br/&gt;
In this context, will we always have unspecified submissionTime  or is there case where submissionTime  is pointing to some incorrect/spurious value (if this is always in the codepath after makeNewStageAttempt; then it should be fine).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Essentially, is the workaround for existing spark versions to simply set submissionTime to current time if it is None for SparkListenerStageSubmitted sufficient ? Will it miss some corner case ? (value is set but is incorrect ?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15954357" author="vanzin" created="Mon, 3 Apr 2017 23:54:09 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I was referring to the case where we are persisting to event log or consuming events to externally persist them.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see. In that case I believe it will always be unset. For live listeners, current time is a good enough approximation, but for the history server, for example, that&apos;s not an option (since &lt;tt&gt;SparkListenerStageSubmitted&lt;/tt&gt; does not have a &lt;tt&gt;time&lt;/tt&gt; field).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15954387" author="mridulm80" created="Tue, 4 Apr 2017 00:14:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For history server that will fail - good point.&lt;br/&gt;
Atleast for custom listeners, users can workaround until next release by using current time (in there code when field submissionTime  is None).&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for clarifying &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vanzin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vanzin&quot;&gt;vanzin&lt;/a&gt; !&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16003471" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 9 May 2017 20:25:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;vanzin&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
